liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The Israeli military says soldiers backed by helicopters killed at least two gunmen who crossed the border from Lebanon. A Hezbollah official says the group had not mounted any operation into Israel. Artillery shelling and gunfire were heard at Lebanon's southern border with Israel, a correspondent for Hezbollah's Al-Manar TV said in a post on social media. In a statement, the Israeli military said its soldiers "killed a number of armed suspects that infiltrated into Israeli territory from Lebanese territory". It did not elaborate on the number. Military helicopters "are currently striking in the area," the statement added. Reuters
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Shelling, gunfire at Lebanon's southern border

children.content: The Israeli military says soldiers backed by helicopters killed at least two gunmen who crossed the border from Lebanon.
A Hezbollah official says the group had not mounted any operation into Israel.
Artillery shelling and gunfire were heard at Lebanon's southern border with Israel, a correspondent for Hezbollah's Al-Manar TV said in a post on social media.
In a statement, the Israeli military said its soldiers "killed a number of armed suspects that infiltrated into Israeli territory from Lebanese territory".
It did not elaborate on the number.
Military helicopters "are currently striking in the area," the statement added.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The European Commission says it is putting its full portfolio of development aid to Palestinians, worth 691 million euros ($1.134 billion), under review and immediately suspending all payments. "The scale of terror and brutality against Israel and its people is a turning point," Oliver Varhelyi, the European Commissioner for the EU's neighbourhood, said in a post on social media. "There can be no business as usual."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: EU freezes aid for Palestinians

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The United States on Monday confirmed the death of nine Americans in Israel. "We extend our deepest condolences to the victims and to the families of all those affected, and wish those injured a speedy recovery," a National Security Council spokesperson said in a statement. "We continue to monitor the situation closely and remain in touch with our Israeli partners, particularly the local authorities." State Department spokesperson Matthew Miller has also confirmed there are unaccounted US citizens still in Israel. Reuters
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: US confirms death of nine Americans
